title: Core i-3 6100
text:
Selling this CPU because I am getting into video editing/rendering and need more cores. Bought this CPU 3 months ago brand new. 

I am very hesitant to sell this CPU because it is such an amazing overclocker.....I know, it's not a K SKU, however, on Z-1/270 boards, the BCLCK is unlocked and I get this thing up to 4.6 stable all day. On Cinebench the single core score is 192, which is faster than any i7 I have seen. This translates into GREAT gaming performance. Runs cool as well. I run it at 4.4 Mhz with the STOCK COOLER at 50C. 

If you are looking to build a gaming computer on the cheap, this is a go to chip. Pair this with a 1050 ti and you are maxing out titles at 1080p. 

If you need proof of any of the claims i'm making, just ask, and I will provide it.

Comes with stock cooler.

title: DD WRT Upgraded Netgear N600
text:
I received a new Nighthawk X6 for Christmas, so my upgraded N600 is now available. It's been a great router - especially after installing DD-WRT on it.

If you're not familiar with that software, it essentially gives you options available only in $600+ routers. The first thing I do when I get a router is install this right away and set it up. There are apps for the Apple iPhone and Android (Droid) that allow you control this remotely - it's amazing to be able to wake up my PC remotely and log into it securely, then turn off port forwarding when I'm done to keep things safe. For what it's worth, I have the app on my wife's iPhone 6 so she can access the webcam in my daughters room when we have babysitters. 

Great router, great app, can't recommend it enough. I may be willing to trade - if you can plug it in or if it's a computer part, feel free to ask. Cash is king, though, and gets first dibs. I can definitely flash it back to the default firmware if you'd like that, as well - I don't know why, but it's not for me to judge. 

Let me know if you have questions - I'm just a tech enthusiast who upgrades frequently and am going through an electronics update - these devices are well maintained and taken care of, and are of high quality. I also have an Asus RP-N53 - N600 Dual-Band Wifi for sale, and can bundle these together if you're looking to upgrade your network to help support new net enabled devices you may have received this holiday season!

title: LTA Luggers 21/24" iMac travel bag
text:
This is LTA Luggers' non-wheeled version of their 24" iMac bag. Though designed for the 24" iMac, my son used it to carry his 2011 21" iMac to his friends' houses on a regular basis. I had cut some dense foam pads to take up the extra space (which I will include) but he almost never used them. The bag worked well as is. Inside the bag are two large padded sleeves that you can use to slide in a keyboard, trackpad, mouse, power cord or whatever. 

Over the course of 3 years he used it a dozen plus times and never damaged the iMac in spite of his being a teen who's not exactly delicate with stuff. The only reason we're selling it is that he's got a different computer now. I'm keeping the iMac and have no need to haul it around.

It's in very good condition. The only damage I could see is a pencil eraser sized snag on one corner which is in one of the pictures.

 Though often described as a travel bag, it's not intended to protect your iMac in a luggage compartment of an airplane or anything like that. I know of some people that have tried to use it that way.

title: CyberPower Battery Backup-New
text:
Got this item for Xmas, did not need. New in Factory box.Product Overview
A mini-tower UPS with line interactive topology, the CyberPower Intelligent LCD LX1500G provides battery backup (using simulated sine wave output) and surge protection for desktop computers, workstations, networking devices, and home entertainment systems. The LX1500G uses Automatic Voltage Regulation (AVR) to correct minor power fluctuations without switching to battery power, which extends battery life. AVR is essential in areas where power fluctuations occur frequently. The LX1500G comes with a three-year limited warranty and a $500,000 Connected Equipment Guarantee.

Battery Backup
Supplies power long enough for equipment to properly shut down when utility power fails. Helps prevent loss of data and minimizes the component stress caused by a hard shutdown.
Surge Protection
Diverts excess voltage away from sensitive electronic equipment during an AC power surge or power spike to prevent damage.
Data Line Protection
Prevents power surges that travel through telephone, coaxial, and Ethernet lines from causing damage to electronics.
Line Interactive Topology
Exists when a line interactive UPS has an autotransformer that regulates low voltages (e.g., brownouts) and over voltages (e.g., spikes) without having to switch to battery.
Automatic Voltage Regulation (AVR)
Provides clean, consistent AC power by automatically regulating low voltages and over voltages, within defined tolerances, when incoming utility power has minor fluctuations.
Simulated Sine Wave Output
Uses pulse wave modulation to generate a stepped, approximated sine wave to supply cost-effective battery backup power for equipment that does not require sine wave output.
GreenPower UPS™ Bypass
Is a patented design that allows utility power to bypass the UPS transformer, when AC power is stable, which reduces energy consumption, noise, and heat buildup.
Multifunction LCD Panel
Displays immediate, detailed information on the battery backup and power conditions, alerting users to potential problems before they can affect critical equipment and cause downtime.
Ultra Quiet Design
Minimizes noise during operation for a quieter work environment.
PowerPanel® Personal Edition Software
Provides a user-friendly dashboard interface for controlling and monitoring the UPS. Free software download available. See the Resources tab.
ENERGY STAR
This model is an ENERGY STAR® certified Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS) system. ENERGY STAR is the trusted, government-backed symbol for energy-efficient products and practices that help save money and protect the environment.
Three-Year Warranty
CyberPower will repair or replace a defective UPS system (including batteries) within three years of the purchase date. See warranty for details.
Connected Equipment Guarantee
CyberPower will repair or replace properly connected equipment if it is damaged by a power surge.

Is a patented design that allows utility power to bypass the UPS transformer, when AC power is stable, which reduces energy consumption, noise, and heat buildup.
Multifunction LCD Panel

Ultra Quiet Design
Minimizes noise during operation for a quieter work environment.
PowerPanel® Personal Edition Software
Provides a user-friendly dashboard interface for controlling and monitoring the UPS. Free software download available. See the Resources tab.
ENERGY STAR
This model is an ENERGY STAR® certified Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS) system. ENERGY STAR is the trusted, government-backed symbol for energy-efficient products and practices that help save money and protect the environment.
Three-Year Warranty
CyberPower will repair or replace a defective UPS system (including batteries) within three years of the purchase date. See warranty for details.
Connected Equipment Guarantee
CyberPower will repair or replace properly connected equipment if it is damaged by a power surge.

All of the "multiple core" equipped Power Macintosh G5 models have three open PCI-Express (PCIe) expansion slots.
